from Bruce Guter: I'm pretty sure that the Desert Hot Springs Photos, taken in 1947, are in fact photos of sites located in Desert Hot Springs in Riverside. The town was founded in 1941 and took off as a resort in the late 40's and 50's , and I would imagine that's why Frasher took photographs there. The focal point of the town then, and I think now, is Pierson Blvd. & Palm Drive. Other photos that we have from this sequence seem to show public buildings like the plunge and municipal water works that were built then.
